The paper discusses machine learning models for medical diagnosis, which suggests that it could fall under several sub-categories. The focus on machine learning and open-set learning suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The use of medical imaging data could also place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses strategies for building ensembles of models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of natural language processing for medical records could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the focus on healthcare applications suggests that it could also fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
